    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1988-05-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1988-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <head>346. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in Hungary<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d346fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Foreign Policy File, D880443–0492. Limited Official Use; Immediate. Drafted
                        by Tongour; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_SJ_2">Jack Seymour</persName>,
                        Jr. (<gloss target="#t_EUR-EEY_1">EUR/EEY</gloss>), Richard Mueller (<gloss
                            target="#t_S-S_1">S/S</gloss>), Paul Schott Stevens (<gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>), Saadia Sarkis (<gloss
                            target="#t_S-S-S_1">S/S–S</gloss>), and Minton (<gloss
                            target="#t_S-S-O_1">S/S–O</gloss>); approved by Simons.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">166021.</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1988-05-24">May 24, 1988, 0553Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <!--<pb facs="d346-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d346-2"/>-->
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Message to New Hungarian Leader.</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Embassy is instructed to pass the following letter from President
                            <persName corresp="#p_RR_1">Reagan</persName> to <gloss
                            target="#t_HSWP_1">HSWP</gloss> General Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_GK_1">Karoly Grosz</persName>. There will be no signed
                        original. We will not publicize this letter, but have no objections if the
                            <gloss target="#t_GOH_1">GOH</gloss> wishes to do so.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Begin text.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Dear Mr. General Secretary:</p>
                <p>I would like to offer you my sincere congratulations on the occasion of your
                    selection as General Secretary. In the name of the American people, I wish you
                    success in your efforts to implement political and economic reforms which will
                    allow Hungary to utilize fully the great talents and creative genius of its
                    people. I would also like to take this opportunity to emphasize the strong
                    desire of the <!--<pb facs="d346-3" n="3" type="facsimile" xml:id="d346-3"/>-->
                    United States to build upon the already good <rs corresp="recLnTb2kD7aAmax9"
                        type="compound-subject">relationship</rs> we enjoy with Hungary. I look
                    forward to meeting with you during your forthcoming visit to the United
                        States.<note n="2" xml:id="d346fn2">July 26–28.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_RR_1">Ronald Reagan</persName>
                </p>
                <p>End text.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SG_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Shultz</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
